Your best is best and combo feeding is what works best for me and my baby. When we decided we wanted to do combo feeding (breast-feeding, bottled breastmilk, and formula feeding) I did tons of research because I only want the very best for my baby. @bobbie had everything I was looking for with an Organic formula. It’s an European-inspired formula crafted in America, delivered right to my doorstep. It’s made with ingredients that are easy on my baby’s tummy with milk from pasture-raised cows, no corn syrup, no palm oil, and no fillers. This formula is sourced from an ethical network of small family owned USDA organic farms around the United States. They are the first formula to receive the clean label purity award and pesticide free certification. It is a Mom-founded and led wholesome company that I feel proud to nourish my baby with! I love this formula with my whole heart!

#fedisbest #formula #organic #Bobbiepartner #BottleBoldly

In my slow living and winter garden era

When I was 8 years old I spent my first very own $12 on a Venus Fly Trap. This core memory will live with me forever. I LOVED that plant, I watched it grow and  cherished it. Since that day, I’m a plat girlie 🪴 My experience at @rootskc last night was nothing short of amazing! Perfect for the holidays, they have something new! You can go in (or doordash same day) this custom gift for your favorite plant lover! Pick any plant that has a bow sticker on it, pick a pot and they will set you up with the cutest gift set with a scooper, dirt and a decantar! Pick the gift bag color and, BAM! Cute custom gift! Great for the holidays or same day birthday, anniversary or just thinking of you gift. 💚
Create Your Own customized gift baskets from @rootskc are such a great idea! 🪴

🌟 Explore, Learn, and Grow with The Inspector Play Kit by Lovevery! 🤩 #LoveveryGift

LC is automatically drawn to the toys in his new Inspector Play Kit from @lovevery . Each plaything is designed to spark curiosity and enhance key skills:

🔵 Ball Drop Box - A magical game of hide and seek, perfect for developing gross motor skills and understanding object permanence.
🌈 Wood Ball Set - Ideal for sensory play, these balls encourage your little one’s hand-eye coordination as they move them in and out of the Ball Drop Box.
📚 ‘My First Signs’ Board Book - Unlock the world of communication with an introduction to sign language.
👀 ‘Things I See’ Texture Cards - These cards are your baby’s window to the world, highlighting everyday objects and potential first words.
🏗️ Nesting Stacking Dripdrop Cups - Foster skills in stacking, building, and understanding containment.
🧩 First Puzzle - A simple yet effective tool for honing fine motor and problem-solving skills.
🎁 Treasure Basket - Explore a variety of items and learn about containment.
🟣 Felt Ball Set - A fun way to learn about movement and texture.
🥤 Drinking Cup - Strengthen those little mouth muscles in preparation for sound formation.

✨ The #lovevery Play Guides are filled with more play ideas, developmental info, and at-home activities tailored for your child’s stage.

Start your journey with The Inspector Play Kit today and watch your little one’s world expand with each play! 🚀
